  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSee https://github.com/axiom-crypto/axiom-apps/issues/6 \r\n\r\nIf the foundry root is `./foo` (so `foundry.toml` is at `./foo/foundry.toml`), while library files are installed to `./lib`, then the remapping `libs = [\"../lib\"]` causes source not found issues when running `forge verify-contract` on etherscan. \r\n\r\nIf I just `cp -r ./lib ./foo/` and then change `foundry.toml` to use `libs = [\"lib\"]`, everything works.",
